  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then into thin slices</p>\r\n<p>Slice the<strong> courgettes</strong>&nbsp;thinly</p>\r\n<p>Add the sliced <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>courgette</strong> to a baking tray season generously with&nbsp;<strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and&nbsp;a pinch&nbsp;of the <strong>oregano</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>then<strong>&nbsp;</strong>pop in the&nbsp;oven until step 6&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook them for 3 min or until beginning to soften</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> cinnamon</strong> and 2/3 of the <strong>garlic </strong>to the tomato pan and cook for a further min, then add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, the remaining <strong>oregano</strong> and a small drizzle of the <strong>vinegar</strong> and stir until combined</p>\r\n<p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to the consistency of a pasta sauce</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/739.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
